proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.description

Class InputParSpec

  • java.lang.Object
    • proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.description.InputParSpec

  • public class InputParSpec
extends java.lang.Object
    The third level of the Description Package, together with OutputColSpec An InputParSpec describes one input parameter and provides the functionality to validate it.

        public InputParSpec(int inputID,
            java.lang.String name,
            java.lang.String description,
            java.lang.String type,
            java.lang.String example)
        Constructs an InputParSpec, setting all its attributes to the specifies values.
        Parameters:
        inputID - The ID of the parameter
        name - The name of the parameter
        description - The description of the parameter
        type - The type of the parameter; this only differenciates between String, int and double, but does not check the length, which would also be included in the meta information
        example - An example value for the parameter

    • Method Detail

      • validate

        public boolean validate(java.lang.String value)
                 throws InvalidInputException
        Checks whether the given value is a valid submission for this input parameter. It does this by checking the type of the parameter, and trying to parse the value into this type (does nothing for String); if predefined values exist, it is checked, that the given value is one of them.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to check
        Returns:
        True, if the value is valid; otherwise an Exception is thrown
        Throws:
        InvalidInputException - If the value is not a valid submission for this parameter

      • checkValueWithPredifinedValues

        public boolean checkValueWithPredifinedValues(java.lang.String valueToCheck)
        Checks whether the given value is one of the predefined values of this input parameter. If there are no predefined values, returns true
        Parameters:
        valueToCheck - The value to check
        Returns:
        True, if this value matches the predefined values of this parameter; false otherwise.

        public void addPredefinedValue(java.lang.String aName,
                      java.lang.String aValue,
                      java.lang.String aDescription)
        Adds a PredefinedValue to the List of PredefinedValues of this parameter. The value is specified by its attributes. This method is used by the Writers to specify their settings.

      • addPredefinedValue

        public void addPredefinedValue(java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> valueDescr)
        Adds a PredefinedValue to the List of PredefinedValues of this parameter. The value is specified by the LinkedHashMap, that is part of the Intern specifying the complete meta information. Checks, whether the LinkedHashMap really describes a predefined value.
        Parameters:
        valueDescr - The LinkedHashMap containing the description of the PredefinedValue
